    "shortDescription": "Lions are the only big cats that actually choose to live together. Their roar isn't just loud, it's a sound you feel in your chest, carrying for eight kilometers across open grassland. The lionesses do most of the hunting while the maned males guard the family, which is called a pride. Fun fact: A lion's roar is so powerful it can travel eight kilometers — farther than most kids walk to school and back."
